nts' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29lg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29lg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>High - pretty much everything Jerry Weinberg has ever published is golden. It comes in roughly two main categories - things you ought to read if you want to pursue a worthwhile career in software, and things you ought to read if you want to be a manager or leader. There is some overlap, but this book falls squarely in the second.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29lg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29lg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29lg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29lg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29lg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29lg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29lg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29lg" href="#29ld" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29lg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29lg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29lg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29lg" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_29ft" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_29ft" class="parent"><a name="29ft" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_29ft" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_29ft" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_29ft" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Yvain/">Yvain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 July 2010 10:51:59PM<em