] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_29ef" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_29ef" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Cyan/">Cyan</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 July 2010 03:59:38PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_29ef'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29ef'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29ef')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29ef" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Tit-for-tat in the iterated Prisoner's Dilemma, specifically. It also poses the question: how good a strategy is it to combine humor with mortal threats?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29ef"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29ef" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29ef')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29ef" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29ef')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29ef" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29ef?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29ef" href="#29e4" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29ef" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29ef')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29ef class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29ef" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_29ef" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_29ef" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2a93" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2a93" class="parent"><a name="2a93" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2a93" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2a93" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2a93" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/khafra/">khafra</a></span></strong></span><s