"#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28so')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28so" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Twinkle, twinkle, little star - <br />
  I know exactly what you are: <br />
  An incandescent ball of gas, <br />
  Condensing to a solid mass.</p>
  
  <p>Twinkle, twinkle, giant star - <br />
  I need not wonder what you are, <br />
  For seen through spectroscopic ken <br />
  You're helium and hydrogen.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Peter Marshall</p>

<p>(Quoted in Robert Ettinger's "The Prospect of Immortality."  Ettinger says that Gene Lund credited it to Peter Marshall. I haven't been able to find a more direct source that confirms this.)</p>

