<p>-L. A. Rollins, <em>Lucifer's Lexicon</em></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28bw"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28bw" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28bw')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28bw" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28bw')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28bw" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28bw?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28bw" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28bw')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28bw class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28bw" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_288z" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_288z" class="parent"><a name="288z" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_288z" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_288z" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_288z" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/brazzy/">brazzy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 09:37:53AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_288z'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_288z')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_288z" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_288z" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/brazzy/">brazzy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 09:37:53AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_288z'>13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_288z'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_288z')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_288z" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>The necessity for marking our classes has brought with it a bias for false and excessive contrast, and we never invent a term but we are at once cramming it with implications beyond its legitimate content. There is no feat of irrelevance that people will not perform quite easily in this way; there is no class, however accidental, to which they will not at once ascribe deeply distinctive qualities. The seventh sons of seventh sons have remarkable powers of insight; people with a certain sort of ear commit crimes of violence; people with red hair have souls of fire; all democratic socialists are trustworthy persons; all people born in Ireland have vivid imaginations and all Englishmen are clods; all Hindoos are cowardly liars; all curly-haired people are good-natured; all hunch-backs are energetic and wicked, and all Frenchmen eat frogs. Such stupid generalisations have been believed with the utmost readiness, and acted upon by great numbers of sane, respectable people. And when the class is one's own class, when it expresses one of the aggregations to which one refers one's own activities, then the disposition to divide all qualities between this class and its converse, and to cram one's own class with every desirable distinction, becomes overwhelming.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/dirs/etext04/mdntp10h.htm" rel="nofollow">H.G. Wells, A Modern Utopia</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_288z"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_288z" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_288z')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_288z" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_288z')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_288z" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/288z?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_288z" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_288z')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_288z class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_288z" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_287a" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_287a" class="parent"><a name="287a" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_287a" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_287a" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_287a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CSmith/">CSmith</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 04:53:11AM</span><span class="votes " >20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_287a'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_287a')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_287a" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_287a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CSmith/">CSmith</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 04:53:11AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_287a'>20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_287a'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points