i><li><a id="parent_t1_28ja" href="#289y" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28ja" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28ja')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28ja class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28ja" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28av" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28av" class="parent"><a name="28av" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28av" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28av" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28av" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jonathan_Graehl/">Jonathan_Graehl</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 04:02:32PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28av'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28av')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28av" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28av" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jonathan_Graehl/">Jonathan_Graehl</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 04:02:32PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28av'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28av'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28av')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28av" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>More likely color-words as concepts exist in the brains of blind people because there are interestingly different distributions of other directly meaningful concepts associated in proximity with others' usage of the color-words, and with actual objects in the world (presuming that their co