_2874')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2874" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>He who knows not and knows not that he knows not is a fool - shun him</p>

<p>He who knows not, and knows that he knows not is a child - teach him</p>

<p>He who knows, and knows not that he knows is asleep - wake him</p>

<p>He who knows, and knows that he knows is wise - follow him</p>

<ul>
<li>Persian proverb</li>
</ul></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2874"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2874" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2874')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2874" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2874')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2874" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/2874?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2874" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2874')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2874 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2874" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2874" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2874" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28hb" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28hb" class="parent"><a name="28hb" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28hb" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28hb" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28hb" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Hariant/">Hariant</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 July 2010 05:02:09PM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28hb'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28hb')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28hb" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28hb" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Hariant/">Hariant</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 July 2010 05:02:09PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28hb'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28hb'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28hb')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28hb" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I've always enjoyed three-fourths of this quote, but the first line still bothers me. If one knows not that they know not, should we not guide them so they at least know that they know not? Then we can teach them, possibly awake them, and finally have more wise people for others to follow.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28hb"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28hb" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28hb')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28hb" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28hb')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28hb" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28hb?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_28hb" href="#2874" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28hb" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28hb')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28hb class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28hb" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_28hb" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_28hb" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28ny" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28ny" class="parent"><a name="28ny" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28ny" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28ny" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28ny" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Kyre/">Kyre</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 July 2010 04:39:55AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28ny'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28ny')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28ny" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28ny" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Kyre/">Kyre</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 July 2010 04:39:55AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28ny'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28ny'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28ny')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28ny" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Good point. I guess the extra effort and subtlety required to guide the obliviously ignorant makes it tempting to just walk away.</p>

<p>Also, the last line presupposes that the knowingly knowledgeable will be wise, which may not be the case if wisdom is taken to have a moral dimension. They could be rational but evil. (Gah - analysing proverbs ...)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28ny"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28ny" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28ny')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28ny" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28ny')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28ny" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28ny?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_28ny" href="#28hb" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28ny" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28ny')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28ny class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28ny" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_28ny" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_28ny" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28nz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28nz" class="parent"><a name="28nz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28nz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28nz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28nz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 July 2010 04:45:00AM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28nz'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28nz')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28nz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28nz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 July 2010 04:45:00AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28nz'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28nz'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28nz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28nz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>'The Master said, “I do not open the way for students who are not driven with eagerness; I do not supply a vocabulary for students who are not trying desperately to find the language for their ideas. If on showing students one corner they do not come back to me with the other three, I will not repeat myself.”'</p>
</blockquote>

<p>--<em>Analects</em> 7.8</p>

<p>If you were in China and were confronted with the top &lt;0.1% of &gt;1 billion, would it be worthwhile to try to teach the ignorant who are ignorant even of being ignorant?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28nz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28nz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28nz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28nz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28nz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28nz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28nz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_28nz" href="#28ny" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28nz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28nz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28nz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28nz" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_284y" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_284y" class="parent"><a name="284y" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_284y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_284y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_284y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/komponisto/">komponisto</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:07:04AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_284y'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcom