<p>-- <em>Mass Effect 2</em></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2895"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2895" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2895')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2895" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2895')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2895" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/2895?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2895" href="#284w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2895" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2895')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2895 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2895" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2895" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2895" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_297n" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_297n" class="parent"><a name="297n" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_297n" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_297n" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_297n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Christian_Szegedy/">Christian_Szegedy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 July 2010 11:59:44PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_297n'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_297n')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_297n" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_297n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Christian_Szegedy/">Christian_Szegedy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 July 2010 11:59:44PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_297n'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_297n'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_297n')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_297n" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I am stunned by the relatively high mod-points of this exchange.</p>

<p>I agree that the quotes are moderately funny. (Albeit the M.S. quote was much more funny in the specific context within the game, but even there it was his white-wash response to an action that earned Shepard renegade points.)</p>

<p>Still, I can't see, how all this is related to the  "art of human rationality"...</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_297n"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_297n" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_297n')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_297n" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_297n')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_297n" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/297n?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_297n" href="#2895" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_297n" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_297n')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_297n class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_297n" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_297n" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_297n" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_29hj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_29hj" class="parent"><a name="29hj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_29hj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_29hj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_29hj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 July 2010 01:47:48PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29hj'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_29hj')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_29hj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_29hj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 July 2010 01:47:48PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_29hj'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29hj'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29hj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29hj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>"Killing is wrong, no matter what," is a very powerful and standard meme for heroes.</p>

<p>It is counter intuitive for someone who "loves people" to kill someone. It requires a less-biased assessment of expected utility than is typically performed. That's why I enjoyed the original quote; in the context of the movie, it made sense in the way of typical human failings for him to say no, and his body language and tone highly suggested he would do so right until the end.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29hj"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29hj" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29hj')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29hj" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29hj')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29hj" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29hj?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29hj" href="#297n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29hj" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29hj')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29hj class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29hj" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_29hj" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_29hj" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_29ma" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_29ma" class="parent"><a name="29ma" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_29ma" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_29ma" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_29ma" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 July 2010 08:19:43PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29ma'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_29ma')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_29ma" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_29ma" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 July 2010 08:19:43PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_29ma'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29ma'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29ma')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29ma" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"Killing is wrong, no matter what," is a very powerful and standard meme for heroes.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>It's also convenient for writers. Imagine what would happen to the Batman comic book series if someone finally got around to putting a bullet through The Joker's brain. (In a Discworld story, it's suggested that "heroes" and Dark Lords have a bit of an understanding: Dark Lords keep on making all of the mistakes on the Evil Overlord list, and heroes keep on letting Dark Lords escape after the day has been saved.)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29ma"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29ma" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29ma')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29ma" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29ma')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29ma" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29ma?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29ma" href="#29hj" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29ma" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29ma')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29ma class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29ma" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_29hm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_29hm" class="parent"><a name="29hm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_29hm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_29hm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_29hm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 July 2010 03:01:17PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29hm'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_29hm')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_29hm" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_29hm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 July 2010 03:01:17PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_29hm'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29hm'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29hm')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29hm" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"Killing is wrong, no matter what," is a very powerful and standard meme for heroes.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And nauseating. Don't forget nauseating.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29hm"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29hm" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29hm')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29hm" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29hm')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29hm" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29hm?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29hm" href="#29hj" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29hm" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29hm')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29hm class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29hm" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_29m5" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_29m5" class="parent"><a name="29m5" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_29m5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_29m5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_29m5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Christian_Szegedy/">Christian_Szegedy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 July 2010 06:59:54PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29m5'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_29m5')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_29m5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_29m5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Christian_Szegedy/">Christian_Szegedy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 July 2010 06:59:54PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_29m5'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29m5'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29m5')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29m5" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>In my reading, the assessment was funny exactly because it was emotional and therefore biased. That's what use of "son of a bitch" suggested as well.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29m5"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29m5" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29m5')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29m5" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29m5')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29m5" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29m5?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29m5" href="#29hj" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29m5" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29m5')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29m5 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29m5" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_29m5" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_29m5" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_29m6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_29m6" class="parent"><a name="29m6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_29m6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_29m6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_29m6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 July 2010 07:23:08PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29m6'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_29m6')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_29m6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_29m6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 July 2010 07:23:08PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_29m6'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_29m6'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_29m6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_29m6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Emotion drives value and purpose; logic is compatible with emotion; Spock is a bad example for rationalists.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_29m6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_29m6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29m6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_29m6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_29m6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_29m6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/29m6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_29m6" href="#29m5" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_29m6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_29m6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_29m6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_29m6" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2882" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2882" class="parent"><a name="2882" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2882" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2882" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2882" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 06:54:35AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2882'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2882')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2882" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2882" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 06:54:35AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2882'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2882'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2882')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2882" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Man's bodily needs are simple, being comprised under three heads: food, clothing, and a dwelling-place; but the bodily desires which were implanted in him with a view to procuring these are apt to rebel against reason, which is of later growth than they.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Al Ghazzali, <a href="http://www.sacred-texts.com/isl/tah/tah07.htm" rel="nofollow">&quot;The Alchemy of Happiness&quot;</a></p>

<p>If he were speaking to us through the <a href="http://wiki.lesswrong.com/wiki/Chronophone">chronophone</a>, we might hear him continue:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Accordingly, as we saw above, they require to be curbed and restrained by the mathematical laws promulgated by the Bayesian Conspiracy.</p>
</blockquote></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2882"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2882" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2882')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2882" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2882')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2882" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/2882?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2882" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2882')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2882 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2882" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2882" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2882" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_289g" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_289g" class="parent"><a name="289g" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_289g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_289g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_289g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nisan/">Nisan</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:16:50PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_289g'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_289g')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_289g" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_289g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nisan/">Nisan</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:16:50PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_289g'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_289g'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_289g')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_289g" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>How wise it was of Al-Ghazzali to recognize, a thousand years ago, that our bodily desires exist only to induce us, in a rather stupid way, to satisfy our needs.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_289g"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_289g" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_289g')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_289g" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_289g')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_289g" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/289g?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_289g" href="#2882" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_289g" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_289g')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_289g class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_289g" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_285g" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_285g" class="parent"><a name="285g" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_285g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_285g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_285g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/WrongBot/">WrongBot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:52:08AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_285g'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_285g')">[+] (19 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_285g" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_285g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/WrongBot/">WrongBot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:52:08AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_285g'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_285g'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_285g')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_285g" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
