<p>I'm quite curious to hear what LW thinks of this one.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_285g"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_285g" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_285g')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_285g" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_285g')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_285g" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/285g?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_285g" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_285g')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_285g class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_285g" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_285g" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_285g" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_285i" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_285i" class="parent"><a name="285i" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_285i" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_285i" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_285i" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:58:44AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_285i'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_285i')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_285i" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_285i" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 12:58:44AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_285i'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_285i'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_285i')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_285i" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I don't think it would be controversial to say that "useless" is <em>way</em> too strong a term for describing shortcomings of computers.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_285i"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_285i" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_285i')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_285i" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_285i')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_285i" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/285i?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_285i" href="#285g" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_285i" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_285i')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_285i class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_285i" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_285i" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_285i" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_289w" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_289w" class="parent"><a name="289w" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_289w" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_289w" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_289w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/NihilCredo/">NihilCredo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 02:05:24PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_289w'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_289w')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_289w" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_289w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/NihilCredo/">NihilCredo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 02:05:24PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_289w'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_289w'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_289w')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_289w" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I can't find the quote's context either, but consider this - why would someone ask Picasso about computers?</p>

<p>If the quote is correct, I wouldn't be surprised if it was in response to something like "Do you believe that computers can [be made to] create art [on their own]?". In which case the quote becomes much less categoric.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_289w"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_289w" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_289w')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_289w" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_289w')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_289w" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/289w?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_289w" href="#285i" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_289w" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_289w')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_289w class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_289w" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_289w" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_289w" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28a9" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28a9" class="parent"><a name="28a9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28a9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28a9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28a9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 02:56:03PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28a9'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28a9')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28a9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28a9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 02:56:03PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28a9'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28a9'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28a9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28a9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Well, in that case, it still sounds to me like <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2eu/open_thread_july_2010/283q">View 2</a>: "Only <em>humans</em> will be able discriminate against art upon learning a computer / monkey / child / prankster made it, pendejo!"</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28a9"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28a9" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28a9')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28a9" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28a9')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28a9" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28a9?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_28a9" href="#289w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28a9" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28a9')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28a9 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28a9" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_28a9" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_28a9" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28bv" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28bv" class="parent"><a name="28bv" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28bv" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28bv" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28bv" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/NihilCredo/">NihilCredo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 05:43:36PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28bv'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28bv')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28bv" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28bv" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/NihilCredo/">NihilCredo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 05:43:36PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28bv'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28bv'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28bv')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28bv" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>But that discussion was about science. Nonhuman science is the same thing as human science, so discriminating is irrational. Nonhuman art is (will) not be (necessarily) the same as human art, and it is quite possible that it will not be at all enjoyable by humans.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28bv"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28bv" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28bv')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28bv" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28bv')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28bv" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28bv?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_28bv" href="#28a9" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28bv" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28bv')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28bv class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28bv" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_28bv" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_28bv" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_28nr" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_28nr" class="parent"><a name="28nr" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_28nr" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_28nr" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_28nr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/soreff/">soreff</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 July 2010 03:00:44AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28nr'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_28nr')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_28nr" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_28nr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/soreff/">soreff</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 July 2010 03:00:44AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_28nr'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_28nr'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_28nr')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_28nr" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Nonhuman science is the same thing as human science</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And the experimental evidence for this is what?</p>

<p>More substantially - it is perfectly possible to have a great deal of difference in the
<em>emphasis</em> placed on various subfields in the sciences.  If we'd gone directly from
vacuum tubes to Drexler/Merkle nanotechnology, do you think semiconductor device
