<p>Seriously, in my line of work, answers only take you a step or two forward.  The lasting value <em>is</em> in the questions, which can be reused over and over again to produce change as a side effect of the answer<em>ing</em>, while the actual <em>answers</em> can be consciously discarded once the process of answering is complete.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_28ad"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_28ad" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28ad')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_28ad" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_28ad')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_28ad" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ev/rationality_quotes_july_2010/28ad?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_28ad" href="#286c" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_28ad" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_28ad')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_28ad class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_28ad" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_286g" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_286g" class="parent"><a name="286g" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_286g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_286g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_286g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 July 2010 03:24:47AM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_286g'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_286g')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_286g" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a